<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-682-318  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 682 318.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  Sept 1 1989 v15 n18 p25(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Making a case for Computing Canada On-line. (managementinformation systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cardiff, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computing Canada On-line ranks as one of the best values in themanagement information systems (MIS) area.andP;  The informationservice can easily be accessed via modem on a seven-day, 24-hourbasis.andP;  Among its valuable features are IBM Canada's productadvisories, Apple Canada's special interest group feature forthose building or maintaining mixed environments and the abilityto save time by downloading the appropriate Word printer driver orfacsimile directly from Microsoft Canada.andP;  Users also have accessto the news from a year's worth of back issues of ComputingCanada.andP;  Another useful feature of the service is the ability tocontact reviewers from each issue's Micro Report for additionalproduct evaluation questions.andP;  The service is available for atypical cost of $49 per year.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Data BasesComputing Canada On-line (Information retrieval system)Information Storage and Retrieval.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>